                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-306" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-306" type="surname" value="ROBSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-306" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ROBSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Eastcheap. On the 5th of April, about five o'clock in the afternoon, I was in the parlour adjoining my shop—I saw the prisoner come in, and lean over the counter—he took out the till, by two or three successive efforts, and put it under his arm—I went and asked what he wanted—he put the till on the counter, knocked on the counter with a penny, and said, "I want a pennyworth of something"—he looked round, and said he did not know what—he tried to rush out of the shop, but I stopped him—there was about 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in the till.</p>
